data.description: Located in a coveted area of Martinsburg off a quiet street with no-through traffic, this beautiful home sits in a peaceful setting close to Lake Thomas and within city limits.  A brick walkway welcomes you through tasteful landscaping as you make your way to the front porch with two separate entrances and to the carport.  This brick rancher features 3 bedrooms (one with en suite bathroom) and two full and one half baths.  The home has two living rooms; one currently used as a formal sitting room with carpet and crown moulding, the 2nd featuring built-in cabinetry and hardwood floors.  You'll be eating in style in the formal dining room, surrounded by ornamental wallpaper and with matching curtains, wainscoting, a brick wall and a built-in cabinet.  The kitchen offers 360° of beautiful white cabinetry for ample storage and granite countertop space to prepare meals and host parties.  Other kitchen highlights are stainless steel appliances, counter-height bar seating, a skylight filling the room with natural light, ceramic tile flooring and an eat-in area.  Exiting the eat-in area through the french doors leads you to a large screened-in porch which includes decorative wood trim, cabinets for storage and countertop space, slate tile flooring and two ceiling fans creating a peaceful breeze.  Exiting the porch to the back you'll enter the fenced-in pool area boasting space for your pool side chairs and a gazebo shading you from the sun.  The pool itself is in working order with a diatomaceous earth pool filter with instructions for operating.  Poolside offers shaded and sunny areas.  There are 4 exits from the pool area; 2 through the fence to carport and the other half of the back yard, and 2 inside the home through the back porch and a side hallway leading to laundry, half bath, carport and kitchen.  The laundry room is spacious with upper and lower cabinets and additional closet storage in the hallway.  The home has an unfinished basement featuring a rear entrance 1 car garage and plenty of space for storage.  A large wood burning brick fireplace located in the basement awaits new owners to have the basement partially finished.  Crown molding, decorative wallpaper, wainscoting, tile and built-in cabinetry can be found throughout the home.  Sellers home warranty with American Home Shield (Gold Plan) is transferable and valid till June 3rd, 2024.  House is wired with ADT Home Security System.  Home would also make a great AirBNB, close to many historic site and various outdoor activities such as hiking and river rafting.  Shopping, dining, schools, and parks and train station are just minutes away, about an hour commute to Washington DC making this property the ideal choice for those seeking convenience without sacrificing peace and quiet.  Don't miss the opportunity to make this beautiful home in Martinsburg, WV, your own.  Schedule a viewing today and discover the perfect balance of city living in a serene setting. Your dream home awaits!
